# Import data sets and clean data
emissions = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pforwork/EC3365/main/emissions.csv", delimiter=',', skiprows=2)
emissions.drop([0, 1], inplace=True)
emissions.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

# Change column names for each country.
def extract_country(column_name):
    match = re.search(r"CO2 emissions, (.*?), Annual", column_name)
    if match:
        return match.group(1)  
    if 'Series Name' in column_name:
        return 'Year'  
    return column_name

emissions.columns = [extract_country(name) for name in emissions.columns]

year_cols = [col for col in emissions.columns if col == 'Year']
emissions.drop(columns = year_cols, inplace=True)

# Add 'Year' column.
emissions['Year'] = range(1980, 2022)

cols = list(emissions.columns)
cols.insert(0, cols.pop(cols.index('Year'))) 
emissions = emissions[cols] 

# Transposed dataframe
emissions = emissions.T
emissions = emissions.reset_index()

emissions = emissions[1:]
emissions.columns = new_header
emissions.rename(columns={'Year': 'Country'}, inplace=True)

Energy Consumption¶

In [9]:
energy = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pforwork/EC3365/main/energyconsumption.csv", delimiter=',', skiprows=1)
energy.fillna(energy.median(), inplace=True)
energy.rename(columns={'Unnamed: 1': 'Country'}, inplace=True)

# Drop rows
energy.dropna(subset=['API'], inplace=True)
energy.drop(columns=['API'], inplace=True)

for col in energy.columns[2:]:
    if energy[col].dtype in ['float64', 'int64']:
        energy[col].fillna(energy[col].median(), inplace=True)
energy.dropna(how='all', inplace=True)

energy_long = pd.melt(energy, id_vars='Country', var_name='Year', value_name='Energy_Consumption')
energy_long['Country'] = energy_long['Country'].str.strip().str.lower()

selected_countries = [
    'Singapore', 'United Kingdom', 'France', 'Japan', 'Canada', 'Australia',
    'Sweden', 'Netherlands', 'Switzerland', 'Belgium', 'Austria', 'South Korea', 'United Arab Emirates', 'Spain',
    'Finland', 'India', 'Brazil', 'China', 'Indonesia', 'Thailand', 'Mexico', 'Philippines', 'Vietnam',
    'South Africa', 'Egypt', 'Nigeria', 'Pakistan', 'Bangladesh', 'Kenya', 'Peru'
]
selected_countries_normalized = [country.lower() for country in selected_countries]

# Convert years to string
selected_years = [1980, 1984, 1988, 1992, 1996, 2000, 2004, 2008, 2012, 2016, 2019]
selected_years_str = [str(year) for year in selected_years]

energy_df = energy_long[
    (energy_long['Country'].isin(selected_countries_normalized)) & 
    (energy_long['Year'].isin(selected_years_str))
]
energy_df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
energy_df['Country'] = energy_df['Country'].str.title()
energy_df

Data Analysis¶

Analyse the general trends of the global energy efficiency, examine the underlying economic drives, and explore the role of energy efficiency in mitigating global CO2 emissions.

  • How has energy efficiency evolved over time?
  • Have both developed and developing countries improved their energy efficiency trends?
  • What are the underlying economic indicators that may affect energy efficiency trends?
  • Can energy efficiency policies mitigate the environmental impact of economic activity by reducing CO2 emissions in the long run?

Energy Efficiency Over time¶

In [21]:
df['Energy_Consumption'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Energy_Consumption'], errors='coerce')

In [22]:
df['Energy_Efficiency_Index'] = df['Energy_Consumption'] / df['rgdpo'] # Calculate energy consumption per unit of GDP output

efficiency_trends = df.groupby(['Country', 'Year']).agg({
    'Energy_Efficiency_Index': 'mean',
    'CO2_Emissions': 'mean'
}).reset_index()

# Plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))
for country in ['Australia', 'China', 'United Kingdom', 'India', 'Germany']:
    country_data = efficiency_trends[efficiency_trends['Country'] == country]
    ax.plot(country_data['Year'], country_data['Energy_Efficiency_Index'], label = country)
    
ax.set_title('Energy Efficiency Index Over Time (Selected Countries)')
ax.set_xlabel('Year')
ax.set_ylabel('Energy Efficiency Index (Lower is better)')
ax.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

Energy Efficiency Index and CO2 Emissions in Developed and Developing Countries¶

In [23]:
# Comparing the energy consumption between developed and developing countries
developed_countries = ['Singapore', 'United Kingdom', 'France', 'Japan', 'Canada', 'Australia', 'Sweden', 'Netherlands',
                      'Switzerland', 'Belgium', 'Austria', 'South korea', 'Finland', 'Spain']
df['Development_Status'] = df['Country'].apply(lambda x: 'Developed' if x in developed_countries else 'Developing')

# Calculate average energy consumption for each group over the years
development_trends = df.groupby(['Development_Status', 'Year']).agg({
    'Energy_Efficiency_Index': 'mean',
    'CO2_Emissions': 'mean',
    'rgdpe': 'mean',
    'pop': 'mean',
    'emp': 'mean',
    'rgdpo': 'mean',
    'Energy Prices': 'mean'
}).reset_index()
In [24]:
# Plot (Energy Efficiency Index and CO2 Emissions for developed and developing countries)
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 14))
# Energy efficiency index
for status in ['Developed', 'Developing']:
    subset = development_trends[development_trends['Development_Status'] == status]
    ax1.plot(subset['Year'], subset['Energy_Efficiency_Index'], label=status)
ax1.set_title('Energy Efficiency Index (Developed and Developing Countries)')
ax1.set_xlabel('Year')
ax1.set_ylabel('Energy Efficiency Index (Lower is better)')
ax1.legend()
ax1.grid(True)

# CO2 Emissions
for status in ['Developed', 'Developing']:
    subset = development_trends[development_trends['Development_Status'] == status]
    ax2.plot(subset['Year'], subset['CO2_Emissions'], label=status)
ax2.set_title('CO2 Emissions (Developed and Developing Countries)')
ax2.set_xlabel('Year')
ax2.set_ylabel('CO2 Emissions (Million of Tons)')
ax2.legend()
ax2.grid(True)
   
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(20, 30))

devider = make_axes_locatable(ax)

merged_df.plot(column='Energy_Efficiency_Index', ax=ax, legend=True, missing_kwds=missing_kwds, cax=cax, cmap='OrRd')

manual_offsets = {
    'France': (2, 2),
    'Switzerland': (8, 1),
    'Belgium': (15, 0),
    'Netherlands': (8, 1),
    'United Kingdom': (2, 2),
    'Austria': (17, 0),
    # Add more countries and their offsets as needed
}

for idx, row in merged_df.iterrows():
    if pd.notnull(row['Energy_Efficiency_Index']):
        x, y = row['geometry'].centroid.x, row['geometry'].centroid.y
        if row['name'] in manual_offsets:
            x_offset, y_offset = manual_offsets[row['name']]
        else:
            x_offset, y_offset = (0, 0)
        x += x_offset
        y += y_offset
        ax.annotate(
            text=row['name'],
            xy=(x, y),
            horizontalalignment='center',
            verticalalignment='center',
            fontsize='small',  # Adjust as needed
            color='black'
        )

ax.set_title('Energy Efficiency Index by Selected Countries')
plt.show()

# Actual & Predicted Energy Efficiency Index Over time 
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Preparing data for regression
df['Year_Numeric'] = df['Year'].dt.year - df['Year'].dt.year.min()
X_time = df[['Year_Numeric']] # Time variable
y_efficiency = df['Energy_Efficiency_Index'] # Response variable

# Splitting data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_time, y_efficiency, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Regression model
time_model = LinearRegression()
time_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predicting on the test set
y_pred = time_model.predict(X_test)
In [41]:

plt.title('Actual vs Predicted Energy Efficiency Index Over Time')
